other_tests.findings: Did not reveal evidence of deep venous thrombosis. Prominent inguinal lymph node (1.5 cm by 0.6 cm by 1.5 cm) on the right side. Borderline enlargement of the spleen (13.3 cm), left and right kidneys measured 12.3 cm and 12.4 cm with markedly echogenic renal parenchyma present bilaterally.
Left ventricular ejection fraction of 60 to 65% and no pericardial effusion.

Marked tubular injury including luminal dilation and loss of brush borders; collapse of capillary loops and proliferation of epithelial cells indicative of collapsing variant of focal segmental glomerulosclerosis. Podocyte injury with diffuse effacement of foot processes.
